div.div: Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu

When a 34-year-old underachiever gets run over by a bus, his story doesnt end there. Reincarnated in a new world as an infant, Rudy will seize every opportunity to live the life hes always wanted. Armed with new friends, some freshly acquired magical abilities, and the courage to do the things hes always dreamed of, hes embarking on an epic adventurewith all of his past experience intact!
(Source: Funimation)
<i>Note: The anime pre-screened its 1st and 2nd episode starting on the 27th of December on the Nico Nico Live Broadcasting and D Anime Store services<i/>

Dororo, a young orphan thief, meets Hyakkimaru, a powerful ronin. Hyakkimaru's father, a greedy feudal lord, had made a pact with 12 demons, offering his yet-unborn son's body parts in exchange for great power. Thus, Hyakkimaru - who was born without arms, legs, eyes, ears, a nose or a mouth - was abandoned in a river as a baby. Rescued and raised by Dr. Honma, who equips him with artificial limbs and teaches him sword-fighting techniques, Hyakkimaru discovers that each time he slays a demon, a piece of his body is restored. Now, he roams the war-torn countryside in search of demons.

Meet the would-be assassins of class 3-E: Sugino, who let his grades slip and got kicked off the baseball team. Karma, whos doing well in his classes but keeps getting suspended for fighting. And Okuda, who lacks both academic and social skills, yet excels at one subject: chemistry. Who has the best chance of winning that reward? Will the deed be accomplished through pity, brute force or poison...? And what chance does their teacher have of repairing his students tattered self-esteem? (Source: Viz Media) Included side stories: Volume 2: Koro-sensei VS Saiki Kusuo: Irumashi Saishuu Kessen Volume 7: Koro-sensei VS Saiki Kusuo: Irumashi Saishuu Kessen II Volume 21: Jitaku no Jikan Volume 21: Izakaya no Jikan Volume 21: Sujou no Jikan Volume 21: Arigatou no Jikan Volume 21: Tokyo Department Sensou Taikenki

In an age when the corners of the world have been scoured for their secrets, only one place remains unexploreda massive cave system known as the Abyss. Those who traverse its endless pits and labyrinth-like tunnels are known as Cave Raiders. A young orphan named Riko dreams of following in her mothers footsteps as a Cave Raider, and when she meets a strange robot when exploring the Abyss, shes one step closer to achieving her goal! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Note: Nominated for the 11th Manga Taishou Awards (2018).
